    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "ABOUT THE ROLE\n\nAt Deliveroo Belgium, our CRM and customer engagement efforts are evolving, and with it, the opportunity for a curious and enthusiastic intern to grow alongside us.\n\nWe are looking for a flexible, eager-to-learn CRM Intern who will play a key role in operational campaign execution and performance tracking, while being fully immersed in how we engage, retain, and grow our customer base.\n\nThis internship is designed for someone who may not yet have a fully defined skillset, but who is excited to understand how customer communications are managed at scale, how data informs marketing decisions, and how campaigns drive business impact. We will support you every step of the way, helping you build strong analytical and operational skills with real impact from day one.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\nCRM Campaign Operations (core responsibility)\n\n - Support the day-to-day execution of CRM campaigns (email, push notifications)\n\n - Build and schedule campaigns in CRM tools, ensuring accuracy in targeting, content, and timing\n\n - Manage and push live customer communications (e.g. promotional messages, lifecycle campaigns)\n\n - Assist in the creation and localization of campaign content across different channels and audiences\n\n - Perform quality checks (QA) before launch to ensure a smooth customer experience\n\n - Act as a key operational link between campaign planning and execution\n\nPerformance Tracking \u0026 Analytics\n\n - Monitor campaign performance (open rates, click-through rates, conversions, retention)\n\n - Support the creation of regular CRM performance reports\n\n - Analyze campaign results and help identify trends, insights, and improvement opportunities\n\n - Assist in A/B testing initiatives and summarize key learnings\n\nExposure to CRM Strategy \u0026 Business Thinking\n\n - Work closely with the CRM manager to understand how engagement strategies are defined\n\n - Contribute to campaign reviews and learn how performance insights inform decisions\n\n - Support preparation of presentations and materials for internal stakeholders\n\nLearning \u0026 Growth\n\n - Gain hands-on experience with CRM tools and customer data\n\n - Learn how to translate data into actionable insights\n\n - Develop a strong understanding of how CRM contributes to growth and customer retention\n\n - Progressively take on more ownership as your skills and confidence grow\n\n\nWHO WE’RE LOOKING FOR\n\nWe are not looking for a “perfect” profile, we are looking for potential.\n\nYou might be a great fit if you are:\n\n - Curious, proactive, and motivated to learn quickly\n\n - Comfortable working with data and interested in analytics\n\n - Organized and detail-oriented (especially important for campaign execution)\n\n - Interested in customer behavior, marketing, and business growth\n\n - Comfortable asking questions and open to feedback\n\n - Able to adapt in a fast-moving environment where priorities evolve\n\n\nREQUIREMENTS\n\n - Currently studying towards a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Belgium (e.g. business, economics, marketing, or similar)\n\n - Available for a 6-month internship (with potential extension up to 12 months)\n\n - Comfortable working in English (French and/or Dutch)\n\n - Basic familiarity with Google Sheets / Excel (data handling)\n\n - Interest in CRM tools or marketing automation is a plus\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL GAIN\n\n - A hands-on, high-impact internship in a fast-growing international company\n\n - Direct exposure to CRM operations, customer engagement, and analytics\n\n - A steep learning curve in both marketing execution and data analysis\n\n - Mentorship and guidance from experienced team members\n\n - A vibrant and friendly office environment in Brussels\n\n - Opportunities for both personal and professional development\n\n - And yes, great food 🍕\n\n\nABOUT DELIVEROO\n\nDeliveroo is on a mission to transform the way people experience food. We combine operational excellence with bold thinking, moving fast while staying detail-oriented. Every day brings new challenges and opportunities to grow, and we’re looking for people who want to grow with us.\n\nThis internship is an ideal starting point for students who want to learn how customer engagement works in practice, develop analytical skills, and make a meaningful contribution early in their career.",
